tly in the application. You can apply formatting styles, add flow text between columns and pages, adjust kerning and even create tables, all within the program. It&#39;s an impressive set of features we&#39;d expect from the best desktop publishing software around.","However, as a desktop publishing package for home use, Viva Designer lacks most of the non-typographical tools you&#39;d want. Where other programs offer hundreds of new fonts to help spice up your documents, Viva has none. It also lacks the plethora of templates and art assets that most of the programs in our desktop publishing reviews are equipped with. It only features nine templates – three brochures and six newsletter templates. If you want to make a different type of document, you have to design it yourself. As such, this software is better designed for people who want to create high-quality, professional documents from scratch. If you&#39;re an experienced graphic designer or have access to stock photos and imagery, this is a program you will want to consider. If you&#39;d prefer a program that comes with thousands of predesigned templates and graphics, you might be interested in <a href=\"/xara-page-layout-review\">Xara Page &amp; Layout Designer</a>.","You can contact Viva&#39;s customer support via email and phone. Unfortunately, there isn’t a lot of online help at the website. Even professionals would appreciate more of a support system, but for more novice users, it is essential.<br/> "]},"id":"e08e032c-a296-4f62-a3c8-c7ae6ca48ab6","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"2f51e23f-b688-4015-b870-098aee7605d3","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Viva Designer is a solid product in its own right. It offers a wide variety of powerful typographical and layout features that make it great for school newspapers and corporate newsletters. But despite marketing itself as a desktop publishing program, Viva Designer&#39;s at-home usability is very limited. Its lack of project templates and even clip art make it best suited for people who have graphics and professional layout skills."]},"id":"1da03f5a-337e-4601-9496-908638482f20","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_59646","url":"/vivadesigner-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"rebecca-spear","url":"/author/rebecca-spear","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Rebecca Spear","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"X8Ccy4LP9pMXtXdurbSshX","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2014-06-04T22:27:48Z","datePublished":"2014-06-04T22:27:48Z","name":"Viva Designer 9.0","synopsis":"Editor's Note: A new version of Viva Designer is now available. Clicking on the buy button will take you to this new version for purchase. We will evaluate and rank this new program when we next update the Desktop Publishing Software site.","review":{"rating":62,"verdict":"People wanting to take on professional design projects, including newsletters, brochures and other business-related publications, will love this software, but it is not well suited for at-home projects.","pros":["Superb typography tools make laying out long articles in Viva Designer a simple task."],"cons":["This program lacks templates, art assets and graphic design tools for novice designers."]},"strapline":"Editor's Note: A new version of Viva Designer is now available. Clicking on the buy button will take you to this new version for purchase. We will evaluate and rank this new program when we next update the Desktop Publishing Software site.","language":"en","dateModified":"2014-06-04T22:27:48Z","id":"QrVcY3UUKNARTVDufQJWYN","meta":{"title":"VivaDesigner Review - Pros, Cons and Verdict","description":"Given that it&#039;s designed for professional use, how does Viva Designer stack up next to the best at-home publishing software around? We find out in our review."},"products":[{"slug":"viva-designer-9-0","url":"/product/viva-designer-9-0","dateCreated":"2019-04-